item.description:
The Storage subsystem is highly modular. These drivers are separated into two logical sets:
DS: Datastore drivers. They serve the purpose of managing images: register, delete, and create empty datablocks. TM: Transfer Manager drivers. They manage images associated with instantiated VMs. Datastore Drivers Structure Located under /var/lib/one/remotes/datastore/&lt;ds_mad&gt;
cp: copies/dumps the image to the datastore ARGUMENTS: image_id STDIN: datastore_image_dump RETURNS: image_source image_format datastore_image_dump is an XML dump of the driver action encoded in Base 64.
